# DataTable

Use `<DataTable>` from `@/components/data-table` for **every** list/table view. Never write raw `<table>` markup.

## Imports

`DataTable` is built on [`@tanstack/react-table`](https://tanstack.com/table) (headless): columns are native `ColumnDef<T>` objects, and the component renders them with `flexRender`. Backend-driven search/pagination/filters (via `useInfiniteList`) and the `Set`-based selection model are unchanged.

```tsx
import {
  DataTable,
  SearchBar,
  SelectAllCheckbox,
  FilterPills,
  NameCell,
  StatusBadge,
  DateCell,
  type ColumnDef,
  type RowAction,
} from '@/components/data-table';
import { checkboxColumn, actionsColumn } from '@/components/data-table-utils';
import { useInfiniteList } from '@/hooks/use-infinite-list';
```

## Data Fetching — `useInfiniteList`

All list tables fetch their own data via the `useInfiniteList<T>(endpoint, options?)` hook. **No server-side data fetching in page components** — pages are thin wrappers that render `<PageHeader>` + the table component.

```tsx
const {
  items,        // T[] — single page of rows
  loading,      // true during fetch
  total,        // total row count from the API
  totalPages,   // total number of pages
  page,         // current page number
  search,       // current search string (raw, pre-debounce)
  setSearch,    // update search (debounced 300ms internally)
  filters,      // Record<string, string> of active filters
  setFilters,   // replace all filters (resets to page 1)
  goToPage,     // navigate to a specific page (syncs to URL)
  refresh,      // re-fetch current page (call after mutations)
} = useInfiniteList<StrategyListItem>('strategies', { limit: 20 });
```

### Options

| Option | Type | Default | Description |
|--------|------|---------|-------------|
| `limit` | `number` | `20` | Items per page |
| `debounceMs` | `number` | `300` | Search debounce delay in ms |

### URL sync

- `search`, `filters`, and `page` are synced to URL query params via `window.history.replaceState` (no Next.js re-renders, no history pollution).
- On mount, the hook reads initial values from the URL so links are shareable/bookmarkable.

### Key behaviors

- `endpoint` is the path segment appended to `serviceUrl()` (e.g. `'strategies'`, `'input-presets'`).
- Search is **backend-powered** — the hook passes `search` as a query param. Never filter client-side.
- `setFilters({ is_active: 'true' })` passes extra query params to the backend.
- After any mutation (create, delete, clone, toggle), call `refresh()` to reload.
- Use `<Pagination>` from `@/components/pagination` in the `footer` prop with `goToPage` as the `onPageChange` callback.

## DataTable Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `columns` | `ColumnDef<T>[]` | — | TanStack column definitions |
| `data` | `T[]` | — | Row data from `useInfiniteList.items` |
| `rowKey` | `(row: T) => string` | — | Unique key per row |
| `rowClassName` | `(row: T) => string` | `'hover:bg-surface-muted'` | Dynamic row classes |
| `emptyMessage` | `string` | `'No items found.'` | Empty state text |
| `loading` | `boolean` | `false` | Show skeleton rows while fetching |
| `toolbar` | `ReactNode` | — | Search/filter bar — rendered sticky at top |
| `footer` | `ReactNode` | — | After-table content (typically `<Pagination>`) |
| `className` | `string` | `'mt-8'` | Outer wrapper classes |
| `skeletonRows` | `number` | `5` | Fallback skeleton count (auto-adjusts to last data length) |
| `enableColumnVisibility` | `boolean` | `true` | Show the built-in "Columns" show/hide menu in the toolbar bar |

### Sticky toolbar

The toolbar is `sticky top-0 z-10 bg-surface` and stays visible while the user scrolls through rows. The outer card uses `overflow-clip` (not `overflow-hidden`) so `sticky` works correctly.

### Pagination footer

Use `<Pagination>` from `@/components/pagination` in the `footer` prop:

```tsx
footer={<Pagination page={page} totalPages={totalPages} total={total} onPageChange={goToPage} />}
```

## Toolbar

Every list table should include a toolbar with a `SearchBar` and `SelectAllCheckbox`.

### Standard toolbar layout

```tsx
const toolbar = (
  <div className="flex items-center gap-4">
    <div className="w-72">
      <SearchBar value={search} onChange={setSearch} placeholder="Search items..." />
    </div>
    {/* Optional: FilterPills for backend-driven status filtering */}
    <FilterPills options={STATUS_OPTIONS} value={statusFilter} onChange={updateStatusFilter} />
    <div className="ml-auto">
      <SelectAllCheckbox count={selected.size} total={items.length} onToggle={toggleAll} />
    </div>
  </div>
);
```

### FilterPills with backend filters

FilterPills are for **backend-driven** filters. When the user clicks a pill, call `setFilters()` to send the filter as a query param:

```tsx
const updateStatusFilter = useCallback((v: StatusFilter) => {
  setStatusFilter(v);
  const f: Record<string, string> = {};
  if (v !== 'all') f.is_active = v === 'active' ? 'true' : 'false';
  setFilters(f);
}, [setFilters]);
```

## Column Definition

Columns are native TanStack `ColumnDef<T>` objects. Each needs a stable `id`, a `header` (string or render fn), and a `cell` that receives `({ row })` and reads `row.original`. Per-column Tailwind classes live on `meta.headerClassName` / `meta.cellClassName` (a `ColumnMeta` augmentation), and `meta.label` overrides the column's name in the visibility menu when `header` is not a string.

```tsx
const columns = useMemo<ColumnDef<Item>[]>(() => [
  {
    id: 'name',
    header: 'Name',
    cell: ({ row }) => <NameCell href={`/items/${row.original.id}`} name={row.original.name} subtitle={row.original.description} />,
    meta: { cellClassName: 'px-6 py-4' },
  },
  // ...
], [/* deps */]);
```

Header/cell default classes (`TH_DEFAULT` / `TD_DEFAULT`) handle padding, text size, color, and `whitespace-nowrap`. Only set `meta.cellClassName` for special cases (e.g. `NameCell` columns use `'px-6 py-4'` to allow wrapping). Always memoize `columns` with `useMemo`.

## Reusable Cell Components

### NameCell — linked name + optional subtitle

```tsx
cell: ({ row }) => <NameCell href={`/resources/${row.original.id}`} name={row.original.name} subtitle={row.original.description} />,
meta: { cellClassName: 'px-6 py-4' },
```

Props: `href`, `name` (string | null), `subtitle?` (string | null), `fallback?` (default `'Untitled'`).

### StatusBadge — consistent status pill

```tsx
cell: ({ row }) => <StatusBadge status={row.original.deletedAt ? 'deleted' : 'active'} />,
```

Statuses: `'active'` (green), `'inactive'` (gray), `'deleted'` (red).
Optional `label` prop overrides the display text.

### DateCell — formatted date

```tsx
cell: ({ row }) => <DateCell date={row.original.createdAt} />,
```

## checkboxColumn Factory

All list tables should include `checkboxColumn()` as the **first** column for per-row selection. The select-all control lives in the toolbar via `SelectAllCheckbox`.

```tsx
checkboxColumn<RowType>({
  selected,
  onToggle: toggleSelect,
  rowId: (row) => row.id,
  isSelectable: (row) => !row.deletedAt,  // optional guard
}),
```

Pair with `<BulkDeleteBar>` from `@/components/bulk-delete-bar` and `SelectAllCheckbox` in the toolbar.

## actionsColumn Factory

Use `actionsColumn()` as the **last** column. Never write raw action button JSX in column definitions.

Each action is described declaratively with `{ icon, label, onClick }`:

```tsx
actionsColumn<RowType>([
  { icon: 'clone',  label: 'Clone item',  onClick: (row) => handleClone(row.id), loading: (row) => cloningId === row.id },
  { icon: 'edit',   label: 'Edit item',   onClick: (row) => router.push(`/items/${row.id}/edit`) },
  { icon: 'delete', label: 'Delete item',  onClick: (row) => handleDelete(row.id, row.name), variant: 'danger', loading: (row) => deletingId === row.id },
])
```

### RowAction descriptor

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `icon` | `'clone' \| 'delete' \| 'edit'` | Built-in icon |
| `label` | `string` | Tooltip text (shown on hover) |
| `onClick` | `(row: T) => void` | Click handler |
| `variant` | `'default' \| 'danger'` | Button style (default: `'default'`) |
| `loading` | `(row: T) => boolean` | Shows spinner when true |
| `hidden` | `(row: T) => boolean` | Hides button when true |

For custom components, use the render escape hatch:

```tsx
{ render: (row) => <CustomActionButton resourceId={row.id} variant="icon" /> }
```

## Column visibility

`DataTable` renders a built-in "Columns" show/hide menu (Radix Popover) on the right of the toolbar bar whenever any column is hideable. Visibility is client-side state held by the table instance. The `select` and `actions` factory columns set `enableHiding: false`, so they never appear in the menu. Pass `enableColumnVisibility={false}` to hide the control. Give a column `meta.label` when its `header` is not a string so the menu shows a readable name.

## Class Name Constants

`TD_DEFAULT` / `TH_DEFAULT` are applied automatically to every cell/header; override per column via `meta.cellClassName` / `meta.headerClassName`.

| Constant | Value | Use for |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `TD_DEFAULT` | `'whitespace-nowrap px-6 py-4 text-body text-text-secondary'` | Most data cells (applied automatically) |
| `TH_DEFAULT` | `'px-6 py-3 text-left text-caption font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-text-secondary'` | Most header cells (applied automatically) |

## Page Structure

List pages are thin server components — all data fetching happens in the table component via `useInfiniteList`:

```tsx
export default function ResourcesPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <PageHeader
        title="Resources"
        subtitle="Description"
        actions={<LinkButton href="/resources/new" iconLeft={<PlusIcon className="size-4" />}>New Resource</LinkButton>}
      />
      <ResourcesTable />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Rules

- Always define `columns` with `useMemo` to avoid re-renders.
- Always include `checkboxColumn` (first) and `actionsColumn` (last) for consistency across all tables.
- Always include a `SearchBar` in the `toolbar` — search is backend-powered, never client-side.
- Use `useInfiniteList` for all data fetching — no server-side fetching in page components.
- After mutations, call `refresh()` (not `router.refresh()`).
- Pass `className=""` when the default `mt-8` spacing is unwanted.
- Prefer cell components (`NameCell`, `StatusBadge`, `DateCell`) over inline JSX.
- Use `actionsColumn()` for all action columns — never write raw action button JSX.
- Give every column a stable `id`; read row data via `row.original` in `cell: ({ row }) => …`.
- Only set `meta.cellClassName` when `TD_DEFAULT` doesn't fit (name columns, custom action cells).
